subject: pswpncopl6
stimulus: Welcome to the experiment. Press any key to begin.

subject: pswpncopl6
stimulus:
In this experiment, you will judge whether most dots are moving

to the right side or the left side.

subject: pswpncopl6
stimulus:
Dot motion will be presented for 1 second. After that, the dots will disappear and you will make your decision.

Which direction are most dots moving?

subject: pswpncopl6
stimulus:
To make your decision, press Q to choose left, press P to choose right.

Remember, your job is to decide which direction most dots are moving towards.

subject: pswpncopl6
stimulus:
Is the dot moving too slow? You can press the same key (Q or P) again to speed up.

The more times you press it, the faster the speed will be.

subject: pswpncopl6
stimulus:
The dot is moving towards the left, however, if you want to choose right instead,

you need to press the P key to reverse the moving direction of the dot.

Once it changes its direction, you can press P again to speed it up.

subject: pswpncopl6
